<HTTPHeadersPermissions-Policy>
<summary>
The HTTP <strong><c>Permissions-Policy</c></strong> header provides a mechanism to allow and deny the use of browser features in a document or within any <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/iframe">iframe</see> elements in the document.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>For more information, see the main <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Permissions_Policy">Permissions Policy</see> article.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Permissions_Policy">Permissions Policy</see><br/>-<see cref="Document.FeaturePolicy."/> and <see cref="FeaturePolicy."/><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy">Content-Security-Policy</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Referrer-Policy">Referrer-Policy</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Permissions-Policy"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</HTTPHeadersPermissions-Policy>
